Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
queryFPlanObject(25.10)                                queryFPlanObject(25.10)

Name
       queryFPlanObject  -  Prints  the  properties of selected objects to the
       console

Syntax
       queryFPlanObject

       [-help]

       [-pd]

       Prints the properties of selected objects to the console. This  command
       supports only instances and modules. You can use this command after se-
       lecting one ore more instances or modules.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each queryFPlanObject parameter. For a  detailed
              description  of  the  command and all of its parameters, use the
              man command:

              man queryFPlanObject

       -pd    Use this option to output power domain information, as  well  as
              check if the objects belong to a power domain.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       Example

       The following commands select and print property information for module
       modA:

       selectInst modA

       queryFPlanObject -pd

Related Information
              * selectInst

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

